Make decisions (if / else)
Add:
age = int(age)

if age >= 18:
    print("You are an adult.")
else:
    print("You are under 18.")
ğŸ‘‰ Commands learned
if / else makes decisions
int() converts text to a number
Indentation matters in Python

Use a loop
Add:
